This metadata report applies to the 2018 ADF&G Salmon Districts. Districts are regulatory areas that divide the Waters of Alaska and the adjacent Exclusive Economic Zone (EEZ) into small units for the purpose of fisheries management.

dataIdInfo.idPurp:
Alaska's commercial fisheries are managed using various regulatory areas (i.e., districts and sections). This data set defines the current valid districts that may be used in commercial salmon fisheries in 2018. This data set should NOT be used for navigation or for determining compliance with ADF&G Commercial Fishing Regulations. Please consult the ADF&G Salmon Commercial Fisheries Regulations for the official definitions of regulatory boundaries.
NOTE: These data attempt to depict boundaries as used for management during a specific time period. In some cases, boundaries used in practice may differ from those described in regulations, reports, maps, and other aids.

scpExt.exDesc: This data quality report applies to the commercial salmon district polygon features and associated attributes published in the PVB_PWS_Districts data set.

dataLineage.statement: The origin of this dataset is PVG_Statewide_1986 (originally named "ADF&G Groundfish/Shellfish Statistical Area Polygons 1986-2000"). Source data was originated by Tim Haverland (ADF&G) and published April 4, 1999.

prcStep.stepDesc: PVB_PWS_1961_GCS_WGS1984 was exported and renamed PVB_Districts_1960_GCS_WGS1984. Polygons were merged by Districts and were aligned to the regulatory coordiantes used in 1960 (S.Larsen).
prcStep.stepRat: The purpose of this step was to create a layer that reflected the commercial salmon districts in 1960.

prcStep.stepDesc: PVB_PWS_Districts_1960 was exported and renamed PVB_PWS_Districts_1961. Polygons were aligned to the regulatory coordiantes used in 1961 and all attribute data were updated (S.Larsen).
